title.narrative: By 2021, National Partners have strengthened technical and management capacity to sustain high-impact maternal, neonatal and childhealth interventions, focusing on the most vulnerable communities.

description.narrative: Atotal of 691,537 beneficiaries were reached (from JanSept 2021) through UNICEF support with high-impact maternal, neonatal and child health interventions, including antenatal, delivery, postnatal and new-born care; immunization against vaccine-preventable diseases; and management of common childhood illnesses such as pneumonia, diarrhoea and malaria. Progress towards accessible quality care was achieved by establishing three additional new-born intensive care units (NICUs) and strengthening existing emergency obstetric and new-born care (EmONC) services. | Status:Met | As-of Date:28/12/2021
